From Mark Wayne Blunier Subject Re W , W , or W Craig Powderkeg DeForest writes If you're planning on making long drives, the W is probably fine esp in the summer in your W car But if you're making short drives, stick to the W Several years ago GM was having trouble with the rings sticking on the diesel They traced a cause to the use of W oil They would not honor warranty work if W was used if my memory serves me , or was OK'd though Mark B